properties.areaDesc: Orange County Coastal; San Diego County Coastal Areas
properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued January 25 at 5:19AM PST until January 25 at 10:00AM PST by NWS San Diego CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Visibility one-quarter mile or less.

* WHERE...Orange County Coastal Areas and San Diego County
Coastal Areas.

* WHEN...Until 10 AM PST this morning.

* IMPACTS...Hazardous driving conditions due to low visibility.
Possible airport delays.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Portions of I-5, I-8, and State Route 163,
among others will be affected this morning in San Diego County,
and I-5 and I-405 in Orange County. The fog may be particularly
dense on some lesser traveled roads with visibility 100 feet or
less.
properties.instruction:
If driving, allow extra time to reach your destination and use
low-beam headlights.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM PST THIS MORNING
